President Donald Trump will award the Presidential Medal of Freedom to Edwin Meese III. The Presidential Medal of Freedom is the highest civilian honor in the United States and is given to individuals who have made significant contributions to the security or national interests of the country, world peace, or cultural and public endeavors. Edwin Meese III, a strong conservative voice, served as Counselor to President Ronald Reagan and played a crucial role in crafting foreign policy that led to the end of the Cold War and securing historic tax cuts. As Attorney General, he promoted Federalism and the original understanding of the Constitution. Meese has continued to advocate for the founding principles of the nation through his work at The Heritage Foundation.